Source: bluefish-unstable
Maintainer: Daniel Leidert (dale) <daniel.leidert@wgdd.de>
Section: web
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), dpatch, autotools-dev, gettext,
 intltool, libtool, libaspell-dev, libgnomeui-dev, libgnomevfs2-dev (>= 2.10),
 libglib2.0-dev, libgtk2.0-dev (>= 2.6), libpango1.0-dev, libpcre3-dev,
 libxml2-dev, libxml2-utils, python-dev, xml-core, zlib1g-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.3
Homepage: http://bluefish.openoffice.nl

Package: bluefish-unstable
Architecture: any
Depends: bluefish-unstable-data (= ${source:Version}), bluefish-unstable-plugins (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: bluefish-unstable-dbg
Suggests: galeon | iceape | iceweasel | www-browser, weblint-perl | weblint, libxml2-utils, php5-cli, tidy
Description: advanced Gtk+ HTML editor
 Bluefish is a GTK+ HTML editor for the experienced web designer.
 Its features include nice wizards for startup, tables and frames; a
 fully featured image insert dialog; thumbnail creation and automatically
 linking of the thumbnail with the original image; and configurable HTML
 syntax highlighting.
 .
 For validation to work you need weblint and xmllint. For preview to work,
 you need a web browser that can view local files given to it
 on the command line.

Package: bluefish-unstable-plugins
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: advanced Gtk+ HTML editor (plugins)
 Bluefish is a GTK+ HTML editor for the experienced web designer.
 Its features include nice wizards for startup, tables and frames; a
 fully featured image insert dialog; thumbnail creation and automatically
 linking of the thumbnail with the original image; and configurable HTML
 syntax highlighting.
 .
 This package contains the plugins. You will need it for the HTML dialogs.
 So it's basically necessary.

Package: bluefish-unstable-data
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Replaces: bluefish-unstable (<< 1.1.5)
Conflicts: bluefish-unstable (<< 1.1.5)
Description: advanced Gtk+ HTML editor (data)
 Bluefish is a GTK+ HTML editor for the experienced web designer.
 Its features include nice wizards for startup, tables and frames; a
 fully featured image insert dialog; thumbnail creation and automatically
 linking of the thumbnail with the original image; and configurable HTML
 syntax highlighting.
 .
 This package contains the architecture independent data.

Package: bluefish-unstable-dbg
Architecture: any
Priority: extra
Depends: bluefish-unstable (= ${binary:Version})
Description: advanced Gtk+ HTML editor (debugging symbols)
 Bluefish is a GTK+ HTML editor for the experienced web designer.
 Its features include nice wizards for startup, tables and frames; a
 fully featured image insert dialog; thumbnail creation and automatically
 linking of the thumbnail with the original image; and configurable HTML
 syntax highlighting.
 .
 This package contains the debugging symbols. Install it to get a better
 backtrace if you observe a crash.
